This is the program 'physics_simulation'.

/* Model an object falling in gravity */
Create 'g' as a double with value 9.81.
Create 't' as a double with value 0.0.
Create 'dt' as a double with value 0.1.
Create 'height' as a double with value 100.0.
Create 'velocity' as a double with value 0.0.

/* Simulate until object hits the ground */
For every iteration of 'step' from 1 to 100:
    If 'height' is greater than 0.0:
        Replace 'velocity' with 'velocity' plus 'g' multiplied by 'dt'.
        Replace 'height' with 'height' minus 'velocity' multiplied by 'dt'.
        Replace 't' with 't' plus 'dt'.
        Call 'printf' with "Time: %.1fs, Height: %.2fm\n", 't', and 'height' stored to nothing.
    Otherwise:
        Call 'printf' with "Object hit ground!\n" stored to nothing.
        /* Early exit conceptually; in this DSL, we continue but skip the 'If' block */
    End if 'height' is greater than 0.0.
End iteration of 'step' from 1 to 100.

End of the program 'physics_simulation'.
